info.header: Nokia Siemens RNC RN60_1 AAL2_sched_perf_new AALSCH measurement dump
info.csv_title: Nokia Siemens RNC RN60_1 AAL2_sched_perf_new AALSCH measurement dump

kpi_info.title: period_duration
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_PEAK
kpi_info.use: The peak amount of sent AAL2 CPS packets in the best effort queue during the measurement period. When the sample of sent AAL2 CPS in the best effort queue is highest. Sampled once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of sent AAL2 CPS packets in the best effort queue during the measurement period. Added to the previous value when data is sampled. Updated once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_SAMPLES
kpi_info.use: The number of best effort queue samples during the measurement period. Updated once per second by the value 1 when statistics data is sampled from the AAL2 best effort queue, but not during periods when the queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_DELAY_PEAK
kpi_info.use: The peak value of delay caused by AAL2 layer buffering in the best effort queue. When the sample of delay in the best effort queue is highest. Sampled once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_DELAY_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of delay values of AAL2 layer buffering in the best effort queue during the measurement period. Added to the previous value when data is sampled. Updated once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_DELAY_SAMPLES
kpi_info.use: The number of sampled delay values in the best effort queue. Updated once per second by the value 1 when statistics data is sampled from the AAL2 best effort queue, but not during periods when the queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_DOWN_MSGS
kpi_info.use: The number of "slow down" messages sent to the MAC layer. When a "slow down" message is sent to the MAC layer to slow down data transmission.

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_UP_MSGS
kpi_info.use: The number of "speed up" messages sent to the MAC layer. When a "speed up" message is sent to the MAC layer to speed up data transmission.

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_STOP_MSGS
kpi_info.use: The number of "full stop" messages sent to the MAC layer. When a "stop" message is sent to the MAC layer to stop data transmission.

kpi_info.title: BE_QUE_DRP_EVENTS
kpi_info.use: The number of events when packets were dropped from the best effort queue. When AAL2 CPS packets are dropped from the AAL2 buffer due to too high delay or buffer overflow in the best effort queue.

kpi_info.title: Q1_QUE_USAGE_PEAK
kpi_info.use: The peak amount of sent AAL2 CPS packets in the scheduling queue1 during the measurement period. UPDATED:When the sample of sent AAL2 CPS in the priority queue is highest. Sampled once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: Q1_QUE_PACKETS_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of sent AAL2 CPS packets in the scheduling queue1 during the measurement period. This counter, divided by the denominator M553C12, provides the average scheduling queue length. UPDATED:Added to the previous value when data is sampled. Updated once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: Q1_QUE_SAMPLES
kpi_info.use: The number of scheduling queue1 samples during the measurement period. UPDATED:Updated once per second by the value 1 when statistics data is sampled from the AAL2 priority queue, but not during periods when the queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: Q1_QUE_DELAY_PEAK
kpi_info.use: The peak value of delay caused by AAL2 layer buffering in the scheduling queue1 . UPDATED:When the sample of delay in the priority queue is highest. Sampled once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: Q1_QUE_DELAY_SUM
kpi_info.use: The sum of delay values of AAL2 layer buffering in the scheduling queue1 during the measurement period. This counter, divided by the denominator M553C15, provides the average scheduling delay. UPDATED:Added to the previous value when data is sampled. Updated once per second, but not during periods when the AAL2 priority queue is empty (i.e. no traffic).

kpi_info.title: Q1_QUE_DELAY_SAMPLES

kpi_info.title: Q1_QUE_DRP_EVENTS

UPDATED:When AAL2 CPS packets are dropped from the AAL2 buffer due to too high delay or buffer overflow in the priority Queue.
